<div class="" id="content">
                      
                      

                        
                            
                            
                                
                                
            
                <h1 id="parent-fieldname-title" class="documentFirstHeading">
                    Make a Gift
                </h1>
            
            
        
                            
                            




                            
                                
                                
            
                <div id="parent-fieldname-description" class="documentDescription">
                   Priorities, opportunities, and ways to give
                </div>
            
            
        
                            

                            


                            <div id="content-core">
                                
    
        
        <div class="" id="parent-fieldname-text-a1d4ff6f5e72836182a37da2703bd820">
            
<p style="text-align: left;">Our progress has been made possible by institutional, governmental,
industrial, and alumni support. Their financial generosity,
intellectual guidance, and enthusiasm sustain our educational and
research mission: within the classroom, across the campus, and around the world.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">The Harvard School of Engineering and Applied Sciences <a href="http://www.seas.harvard.edu/about-seas/giving/gift-opportunities" class="internal-link" title="Gift Opportunities">strongly values
current use funds.</a></p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Such gifts give SEAS the flexibility to
respond to immediate financial needs and support its core mission:
teaching, research, and translation.</p>
<h2 style="text-align: left;">Ways to Give<br>
</h2>
<div id="parent-fieldname-text" class="kssattr-atfieldname-text kssattr-templateId-widgets/rich kssattr-macro-rich-field-view inlineEditable">
<h3><strong>Give Online </strong></h3>
<strong>       </strong>
<p> The University's online donation site is secure and easy to use. We 
accept        MasterCard, Visa, Discover, and American Express. <a class="external-link" href="https://secure.post.harvard.edu/olc/pub/HAA/onlinegiving/showGivingForm.jsp?form_id=63150"><strong>Go        to online giving.</strong></a></p>
<p class="callout"><em>Be sure to indicate your intention to direct the gift to the Harvard School of Engineering and Applied Sciences.</em></p>
<h3><strong>Mail Your Gift</strong></h3>
<p>
<strong>         </strong>If you prefer to give your contribution by
mail, you may send your check, money order, or credit card
authorization to the address below. Please do not send cash. Checks and
money orders should be made payable to: <strong>Harvard School of Engineering and Applied Sciences</strong>.</p>
<p>
Harvard School of Engineering and Applied Sciences<br>Office for Resource Development<br>
Maxwell Dworkin<br>33 Oxford Street<br>Cambridge, MA 02138</p>
<h3><strong>Gifts of Securities &amp; Mutual Funds</strong></h3>
<p>
Making a gift of securities is both simple and tax efficient because
you receive a double tax benefit. With a gift of appreciated
securities, you are entitled to a federal income tax charitable
deduction if you itemize your return. For appreciated securities held
longer than one year, you may deduct the full fair market value of your
gift. A second tax benefit with a gift of appreciated securities is
that you avoid any capital gains tax.</p>
<p>To make a gift of stocks, bonds, or mutual funds, please call the
Harvard Management Company toll-free at (866) 845-6596.</p>
<h3><strong>Planned Gifts</strong></h3>
<p>A planned gift can enable you to support SEAS (including gifts 
through the College and GSAS) while providing income and tax benefits to
 you and your family. Through gift planning vehicles such as <a title="Bequests" href="http://alumni.harvard.edu/give/college/gift-planning/bequests" target="_self">bequests</a> and <a title="Life Income Gifts" href="http://alumni.harvard.edu/give/college/gift-planning/gifts-that-pay">life income gifts</a>, you can address personal financial goals and make a meaningful gift to Harvard.<br><br>Individuals who have planned a bequest or donated a life income gift are welcomed into the <a title="The John Harvard Society" href="http://alumni.harvard.edu/give/college/gift-planning/john-harvard-society" target="_self">John Harvard Society</a>.</p>
<p>For more information, please contact the <a class="external-link" href="http://www.alumni.harvard.edu/give/college/gift-planning">Office of Gift Planning</a> at (617) 495-5040</p>
<h2>Learn More</h2>
<div id="parent-fieldname-text" class="kssattr-atfieldname-text kssattr-templateId-widgets/rich kssattr-macro-rich-field-view inlineEditable">
<p>To learn more about supporting the Harvard School of Engineering and Applied Sciences please contact:</p>
</div>
<p><a class="external-link" href="mailto:danielle_festino@harvard.edu"><strong><span class="textHeader1">Danielle R. Festino</span></strong></a><br>Associate Director of Resource Development<br>
                    (617) 495-9467</p>
</div>

            
        </div>
    
    

